# Skills (skills/)

- Skills are self-contained. Scripts, libs, references, and templates live under
  the skill directory. No `$REPO_ROOT` sourcing, no `../..` escapes.
- No source-repo skill bridges. Do not create `.agents/skills/`,
  `.codex/skills/`, `.claude/skills/`, `.pi/skills/`, or
  `.antigravitycli/skills/` — those duplicate the global install here.
- `SKILL.md` is the task-specific judgment and workflow contract. Keep it
  focused; put large detail in `references/`.
- Skills must be harness-agnostic: filesystem + `SKILL.md` portable across omp,
  Claude Code, Codex, Pi, Goose, and OpenCode. Runtime features are
  optimizations, not dependencies.
- No claim primitives under `skills/`. No semantic workflow engine around
  provider CLIs.
- A new skill must pass the primitive test in `skills/harness-engineering/SKILL.md`
  (prompt vs skill vs doctrine line vs Mode B).
